    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-05-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-05-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="93"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d93">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/873a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-05-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">May, 6, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In the judgment of the Legation, and in the light of the more recent reports from
                    our consuls, how far is the situation in China responsive to the conditions of
                    recognition of governments under international law; and, specifically, in what
                    respects does the Provisional Government still fall short of the
                    requirements?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
